Reposted from @c_c_s_o
 August 21, 2021 will go down as a historic day in Cullman County, AL. I was honored to represent the Cullman County Sheriff’s Office and welcome the 45th President of the United States, Donald J. Trump, to Cullman County. 

As Sheriff of Cullman County, and on behalf of the citizens of Cullman County, I was privileged by the power and authority under the constitution as Sheriff to present President Donald J. Trump with an engraved wooden plaque commissioning him as a deputy sheriff of Cullman County. This plaque thanked President Trump for all his accomplishments for law enforcement as President of the United States. 

I would also like to thank Paul Moss of Southern Heritage Restoration and Wendy Kirk of Initial Impressions for their hard work on the engraved wooden plaque.
